  <body>
    <h2>
      How to test</h2>
    Remember...this is just a sample.<br>
    <ol>
      <li>Start mongoDB with all defaults</li>
      <li>Makde sure you add this portlet to a private page or else
        access it as any authenticated user<br>
      </li>
      <li>Select Admin tab</li>
      <li>Enter any random string as VIN</li>
      <li>Fill out the form and save</li>
      <ul>
        <li>Connect to "test" db of mongodb</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
        <li>You should see "cars" collection with the car entry in
          mongodb</li>
      </ul>
      <li>Enter as many new cars as you want</li>
      <li>If you enter an existing VIN, then you may edit the data
        entered earlier<br>
      </li>
      <li>Select "Store" tab and see the cars <br>
      </li>
      <li>Click on "Like"</li>
      <ul>
        <li>Verify in mongoDB that the "likedCars" array is filled with
          the VINs for the cars you have liked<br>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <li>Select "My Profile" tab and see the cars you have liked&nbsp;</li>
      <ul>
        <li>At this point, you may verify in mongoDB that a user is
          created in "testuser" collection<br>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <li>You may enter first and last name and save to see your changes
        in mongoDB</li>
      <li>Unlike a car and verify in mongoDB that it has been removed
        from the "likedCars" array in the user entry.<br>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <br>
    <br>
  </body>
</html>
